    <h2>Warrandyte — Bushed Yarra Setting, Fire Risk, Annual Cleaning Essential</h2>
    <div class="local-box"><p>Warrandyte sits along the Yarra River in a heavily bushed setting — one of Melbourne's most fire-aware communities. Most homes are on larger blocks with established native vegetation, and many rely entirely on wood heating through winter. Warrandyte is classified under the Bushfire Management Overlay, which makes chimney maintenance here more than routine comfort — it is a genuine fire prevention measure. We frequently service Warrandyte chimneys that haven't been touched in years. The bushed setting means significant debris accumulation in chimney pots, and the cooler river corridor temperatures accelerate creosote formation.</p></div>
